definitions.definition: ( geometry ) A flat surface extending infinitely in all directions (e.g. horizontal or vertical plane); a bounded portion thereof.

subdefinitions.definition: ( anatomy ) An imaginary plane which divides the body into two portions.

definitions.definition: A level of existence or development.
A roughly flat, thin, often moveable structure used to create lateral force by the flow of air or water over its surface, found on aircraft, submarines, etc.
( computing , Unicode ) Any of 17 designated ranges of 2 (65,536) sequential code points each.

definitions.definition: ( countable , carpentry ) A tool for smoothing wood by removing thin layers from the surface .

main_definition: ( countable , carpentry ) A tool for smoothing wood by removing thin layers from the surface .

definitions.definition: ( entomology ) Any of various nymphalid butterflies, of various genera, having a slow gliding flight.
( entomology ) The butterfly Bindahara phocides , family Lycaenidae , of Asia and Australasia.

definitions.definition: A deciduous tree of the genus Platanus .
